The Police on Monday arraigned a 43-year-old man, Sulu Saka, in a Badagry Chief Magistrates’ Court in Lagos State for allegedly threatening his neighbour’s life. Saka, who has no fixed address, is facing a two-count charge of stealing and a breach of public peace. READ ALSO:  Court forecloses statutory rights of estranged housewife to cross-examine husband He, however, denied committing the offences. The prosecutor, ASP Clement Okuiomose, told the court that the defendant committed the offences on Feb.2, at 5:00p.m., at Obele Imagbon area in Lagos State. Okuoimose said that the defendant conducted himself in a manner likely to cause a breach of the peace by threatening the complainant, one Mumini Mojeed. He said that Saka unlawfully threatened the complainant by words of mouth. The prosecutor said that the offences contravened Sections 168 and 42 of the Criminal Laws of Lagos State, 2015. The chief magistrate, Mr Segun Aka-Bashorun, admitted the defendant to bail in the sum of N100, 000 with two sureties in like sum. He adjourned the case until Feb.20 for further hearing.